India Hits Back After Collapsing to 201 All Out on Day One of Second Test

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-06-28T23:29:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/india-hits-back-after-collapsing-to-201-all-out-on-day-one-of-second-test.html
Top-ranked  India  reduced West Indies
to 30-3 on the opening day of the second cricket Test after
suffering two batting collapses to be all out for 201.  The touring team, which leads the best-of-three series 1-0,
removed Adrian Barath, Lendl Simmons and Darren Bravo in the
final session at the Kensington Oval in Bridgetown, Barbados.  West Indies bowlers Devendra Bishoo, Ravi Rampaul and Fidel Edwards earlier claimed three wickets apiece as India slumped to
44-4 at lunch and then 201 all out after losing its last five
wickets for 34 runs. VVS Laxman top scored with 85.  India has never won two Tests in a series in the Caribbean.
The final match is scheduled July 6-10 in Dominica.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
